last_episode_to_air.overview: Tamar doesn't know who to trust. A cat-and-mouse game leads to deadly consequences.

name: Tehran
overview: Tamar is a Mossad hacker-agent who infiltrates Tehran under a false identity to help destroy Iran's nuclear reactor. But when her mission fails, Tamar must plan an operation that will place everyone dear to her in jeopardy.
tagline: Once you're in, there's no way out.

episodes.name: Emergency Landing in Tehran
episodes.overview: Tamar Rabinyan, a gifted hacker and a Mossad agent, enters the heart of Tehran to neutralize army radar systems and enable Israel’s air force to bomb Iran’s nuclear reactor.

episodes.name: Blood on Her Hands
episodes.overview: Tabrizi, a local Mossad agent, tries to help Tamar in any way possible, while Revolutionary Guard officer Faraz is hot on Tamar's trail.

episodes.name: Yasamin's Girl
episodes.overview: Hiding with her aunt, Tamar goes underground and attempts to escape Iran. Faraz and Tabrizi broaden their searches for her.

episodes.name: Shakira and Sickboy
episodes.overview: When she finds a commune of young regime opponents, Tamar takes refuge with them—and becomes close with Milad.

episodes.name: The Other Iran
episodes.overview: At an underground rave with Milad and the other commune members, Tamar must prove her loyalty. Faraz and Tabrizi reach a boiling point.

episodes.name: The Engineer
episodes.overview: Tamar and Milad return to Tehran and blackmail their electric company contact. Kadosh tries to convince Gorev to approve Tamar's new plan.

episodes.name: Tamar's Father
episodes.overview: The incident at the commune leaves Tamar shattered. Kadosh tries to help her recover so they can set the power plant operation in motion.

episodes.name: Five Hours Until the Bombing Run
episodes.overview: With Israeli planes approaching the reactor, Tamar, Milad, and Kadosh launch an operation as Faraz closes in on them.
Free of the Mossad and preparing to start a new life in Canada, Tamar is drawn back in by an irresistible offer.

episodes.name: Change of Plan
episodes.overview: A distraught Tamar chooses to stay in Tehran and seek justice—but learns the Mossad has put Marjan Montazemi in charge.

episodes.name: PTSD
episodes.overview: Determined to neutralize Faraz, Marjan makes a risky move. Tamar finds a way to get closer to Mohammadi. Milad begins behaving irresponsibly.

episodes.name: The Rich Kids
episodes.overview: Tamar attends an elite pool party to target Peyman. Marjan reconsiders the orders she's been given about Faraz.

episodes.name: Double Fault
episodes.overview: When Milad is arrested by Tehran police, Tamar and Faraz each race to reach him. Going against orders, Tamar continues pursuing Mohammadi.

episodes.name: Faraz's Choice
episodes.overview: In a dire situation, Faraz makes a difficult decision. Tamar and Peyman continue getting closer as Milad begins to question her priorities.

episodes.name: Betty
episodes.overview: Peyman tells Tamar about his father's car race, leading the Mossad to devise a plan to take out Mohammadi once and for all.

episodes.name: Blood Funeral
episodes.overview: Tamar doesn't know who to trust. A cat-and-mouse game leads to deadly consequences.
